    <name>5 Basic Steps to Support the Writing Process </name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;These 5 steps can be applied to
any writing topic. Here, we are focusing on how to apply them to help your
learners write their own story. You can create a handout or post the steps in
your classroom or online platform for learners to reference.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prewriting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Researching
&amp;amp; Organizing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drafting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Revising&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Editing
and Proofreading&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;









&lt;p&gt;At each step, provide ways to share
writing, obtain input, and share mastery feedback. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/octae-icon-protips.png" alt="" width="65" height="63" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;Pro Tip:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9826@$" target="_blank"&gt;Use
prompts or sentence-starters.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider-wave-1%20%282%29.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
